/* In order to use this template you should be familiar with how CSS is coded, and what properties */
/* can be assigned to the different elements listed in this template. In a few of them I have left the */
/* properties written out to provide some examples, or to provide a few not as obvious edits that */
/* You may or may not want to keep. */

/* If you already know what you want to edit, but is unsure of the correct name of the element you */
/* need to target, you can quick search this document using CTRL+F (Win) / CMD+F (Mac) and find it */
/* with a simple keyword search. All elements are commented with a short explanation of what they */
/* do. */

/* If you are new to CSS coding, I recommend you keep the WA Codex Guide to CSS Formatting near, */
/* you can find it at https://www.worldanvil.com/w/WorldAnvilCodex/a/css . I also recommend that */
/* you write the code in a CSS parser software, such as Notepad++ or Sublime, and not directly into */
/* the WA's CSS box directly. */


/* =||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||= */
